// Listen for mira_speech events (streamed text from AI)
useEffect(() => {
  const handleSpeech = (data: { text?: string; is_chunk?: boolean }) => {
    // Fallback session detection
    if (!sessionActive && !isStarting) {
      setSessionActive(true);
      setIsStarting(false);
      avatar.startSession();
      stt.startListening();
    }

    if (data.is_chunk !== false) {
      // Still accumulating — skip empty chunks
      if (!data.text) return;
      console.log("[Mirror] mira_speech chunk received");
      responseAccumulatorRef.current += data.text;
      avatar.setAvatarState("thinking");
    } else {
      // End of message — accumulate any final text, then deliver
      if (data.text) {
        responseAccumulatorRef.current += data.text;
      }
      const fullText = responseAccumulatorRef.current;
      responseAccumulatorRef.current = "";
      console.log("[Mirror] Agent full response:", fullText);
      if (!fullText) return;

      // Check for scripted response match
      const scripted = findScriptedResponse(fullText);

      if (scripted) {
        // Play pre-recorded video with baked-in audio (perfect lip sync)
        console.log("[Mirror] Scripted match:", scripted.phrase);
        avatar.playScripted(scripted.video);
      } else {
        // No match — detect emotion for avatar state, then TTS per sentence
        const emotion = detectEmotion(fullText);
        avatar.setAvatarState(emotion);

        // Feed full text through sentence buffer for per-sentence TTS
        sentenceBuffer.feed(fullText);
        sentenceBuffer.flush();
      }
    }
  };

  socket.on("mira_speech", handleSpeech);
  return () => {
    socket.off("mira_speech", handleSpeech);
  };

# Fix: Backend responds but frontend never plays voice/avatar

## Context

The backend IS generating Claude responses — server logs show `[mira] AGENT SAID: ...` with full text. But the frontend plays no voice and shows no avatar lip sync. The browser console shows zero `mira_speech`-related logs (no `[Mirror] Agent full response:`, no `[SentenceBuffer]`, no `[TTS]`).

## Root cause: `!data.text` guard kills end-of-message signal

**File:** `frontend/src/app/mirror/page.tsx`, line 128

```typescript
const handleSpeech = (data: { text?: string; is_chunk?: boolean }) => {
  // ...fallback session detection...

  if (!data.text) return;          // ← LINE 128: "" is falsy → exits!

  if (data.is_chunk !== false) {
    responseAccumulatorRef.current += data.text;     // chunks accumulate fine
    avatar.setAvatarState("thinking");
  } else {
    // End-of-message — flush to TTS                 ← NEVER REACHED
    const fullText = responseAccumulatorRef.current;
    sentenceBuffer.feed(fullText);
    sentenceBuffer.flush();
  }
};
```

The backend sends two kinds of `mira_speech` events:
- **Chunks**: `{"text": "some words", "is_chunk": true}` — pass the guard fine
- **End-of-message**: `{"text": "", "is_chunk": false}` — `""` is falsy in JS → dropped

All chunks accumulate silently in `responseAccumulatorRef`, but the end-of-message signal that triggers `sentenceBuffer.feed()` → TTS → avatar is completely dropped.

## Confidence: Very high

This is a direct code trace, not speculation:
1. `orchestrator.py:306` sends `_stream_text(user_id, "", end_of_message=True)`
2. `_stream_text` emits `{"text": "", "is_chunk": false}`
3. Frontend line 128: `if (!data.text) return` — `!""` is `true` in JS → exits
4. Lines 134-157 (sentence buffer → TTS) never execute

## Proof: test that reproduces the bug

Write `frontend/src/__tests__/mira-speech-handler.test.ts` that extracts and tests the handler logic:

```typescript
// Simulate the exact handler behavior from page.tsx
// 1. CURRENT (buggy): !data.text guard before is_chunk check → end-of-message dropped
// 2. FIXED: guard scoped to chunk branch only → end-of-message processed
```

The test sends simulated streaming events (chunks + end-of-message) and asserts the sentence callback fires. This test will FAIL with the current code pattern and PASS with the fix.

## Fix

### 1. `frontend/src/app/mirror/page.tsx` — Fix the guard logic (line 128)

Move the `!data.text` check inside the chunk branch. The end-of-message branch must always run:

```typescript
if (data.is_chunk !== false) {
  if (!data.text) return;                            // Only skip empty chunks
  console.log("[Mirror] mira_speech chunk received");
  responseAccumulatorRef.current += data.text;
  avatar.setAvatarState("thinking");
} else {
  if (data.text) {
    responseAccumulatorRef.current += data.text;
  }
  const fullText = responseAccumulatorRef.current;
  responseAccumulatorRef.current = "";
  console.log("[Mirror] Agent full response:", fullText);
  if (!fullText) return;                             // Nothing accumulated → skip
  // ... scripted response check, sentence buffer, TTS (unchanged)
}
```

### 2. `frontend/src/__tests__/mira-speech-handler.test.ts` — Regression test

Test the mira_speech handler logic by simulating the streaming event sequence:
- Send 3 chunk events with text
- Send 1 end-of-message event with `text: ""`
- Assert sentence callback was called with the accumulated text

### 3. `backend/agent/orchestrator.py` — Add logging at silent returns

- `handle_event`: log when session not found (currently silent `return`)
- `_call_claude`: emit fallback error message to frontend when Claude API fails

### Files to modify

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `frontend/src/app/mirror/page.tsx` | Fix `!data.text` guard (line 128), add chunk logging |
| `frontend/src/__tests__/mira-speech-handler.test.ts` | New regression test for the handler logic |
| `backend/agent/orchestrator.py` | Add logging at silent returns, emit fallback on Claude API failure |

## Verification

1. `cd frontend && npx vitest run` — new test passes
2. `cd frontend && npx tsc --noEmit` — no type errors
3. Start backend + frontend, open `/mirror?user_id=...`, click Start Session
4. Frontend console should now show:
   - `[Mirror] mira_speech chunk received` — for each streamed chunk
   - `[Mirror] Agent full response: ...` — full accumulated text
   - `[SentenceBuffer] Sentence: ...` — per-sentence TTS
   - `[TTS] Sending to ElevenLabs: ...` — TTS proxy call
5. Audio plays through speakers, avatar switches to talking state

